Target: OntoLandUse is an ontology developed for representing different types of land use code used for rural payment services.

Comment: Code used by land owners to declare what their land is used for, when applying for a rural payment scheme (like the Basic Payment Scheme (BPS) and Countryside Stewardship (CS))
The physical material at the surface of the Earth

Specifies the category to which the code applies to, out of the following: agriculatural land; non-agricultural land; codes for the Countryside Stewardship (CS); or if the code is ineligible for the Rural Payments Service (RPS)

Agricultural land is typically land devoted to agriculture, the systematic and controlled use of other forms of life - particularly the rearing of livestock and production of crops - to produce food for humans.
Land upon which no agricultural activities are conducted and from which no agricultural products are derived

An administrative division is a portion of a country or other region delineated for the purpose of administration. Administrative divisions are granted a certain degree of autonomy and are usually required to manage themselves through their own local governments
Relates the Land Use Code to the physical material present on the surface of that land area
Relates the Land Use Code to the Land Use Code Type, which is used to categorise the Land Use Code

Domain: Land Use Code UNION Land Use Code Type
Comment: Associates the Land Use Code and its Land Use Code Type to the particular region in which it is used
